verbose_text: In contrast, Bilsborough et al. reported that mice deficient in IL-31RA exhibited increased responsiveness to OSM (oncostatin M) and enhanced production of OSM inducible cytokines, such as IL-6 and VEGF, during airway sensitization and challenge, suggesting that susceptibility of IL-31RA -/- mice to exacerbated Th2-type diseases is an indirect result of IL-31RA deletion that leads to an elevated responsiveness to OSM.
evidence: IL-31RA exhibited increased responsiveness to OSM (oncostatin M) and enhanced production of OSM
